      'The theological question Zilpah raises is whether a faith tradition can be built on the unacknowledged labor of people whose faith the tradition never bothered to document. Two of the twelve tribes of Israel descend from Zilpah. Those tribes worship Yahweh, receive land, produce judges and warriors. None of that erases the fact that the woman who bore their ancestors had no voice in the narrative that claims to tell God\'s story. For anyone whose contribution to a community of faith has been essential and invisible — whose work sustained the institution while the institution told someone else\'s story — Zilpah is the ancestor you did not know you had.',
